  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of citations, \"Performing Hysteria\" has potential visibility through platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, indicating commercial interest that may enhance its public reach. However, the lack of community discourse or social media interactions suggests limited engagement in broader scholarly or public discussions.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published by Leuven University Press in 2020, \"Performing Hysteria\" currently has not garnered any formal citations according to available metrics. This lack of academic uptake may reflect a new or niche topic that has yet to resonate within wider scholarly circles. Despite this, the presence of the work on major commercial platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads demonstrates some level of public visibility and interest, potentially indicating that there is an audience seeking to engage with its themes.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book's current lack of online mentions or discussions in vibrant community spaces\u2014such as Reddit, Wikipedia, or Bluesky\u2014highlights an opportunity for increased scholarly engagement and public discourse. Without these metrics, it appears that \"Performing Hysteria\" has yet to ignite conversations that typically signify a book\u2019s penetration into both academic and general audiences.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the impact signals related to community and academic discourse are low, this does not diminish the potential relevance of the work. If it were to gain traction, future metrics could reflect a shift in its visibility and influence. Further promotional efforts, engagement in public discussions, or appearances in academic conferences may facilitate a growing acknowledgment of its contributions to the field.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">In conclusion, while \"Performing Hysteria\" presently shows mini